377:
Our Children's Playground (9-11 Tribute):

Nine eleven, they tell you to die in order to get to heaven where 72 virgins allegedly await.
Iron birds of pray descend from the fiery skies below and you wonder why in total disbelief.
Maybe we do not see eye to eye underneath the same sky.
Maybe we are both deceived to believe different lies in something that perhaps does not exist?
Maybe who you are is not what I am
but what does any of that matter.
How can you hate those you do not know?
Your children and our children would
grow up in friendship
if not for our own blind ignorance and hatred.
A reign of terror fell upon us that day.
Who is to blame?, who is left to hate?
Your children as well as ours were left crying in the ashes to ashes, concrete dust to dust.
Mankinds creation destroyed by
Mankinds evil deviation.
Humanity, we have a long journey of growth before we can bury our ignorance for good.
Those temples were our temples, they were your temples and eventually
they would have been our children's inheritance.
That day was my day and it was your day and someday they will look back
and ponder, that would have been our children's day as well, life is precious.
The hatred that was released on September 11th 2001 will one day consume us all,
causing us to fall alongside the towers, burying us forever if we remain on our current path.
Sure, we can rebuild them but we can never replace the lives.
Sorrow forever hides until it is released by the love outside. Standing tall side by side with love from the inside out. Open your eyes and bury the hatred for good once and for all.
More importantly today, we must rebuild our hearts to love one another
as commanded by our father, let that be our new foundation upon which to rebuild.
Peace, Love and Hope.
May that be our everlasting tribute to the lives lost that horrific, fateful day.
Peace, Love and Hope.
May that be our children's playground for generations to come.
Speak of peace and it will manifest as such.
Peace is always better than war.
Speak of love and it will manifest as such.
Love is always better than hate.
Speak of hope and it will manifest as such.
Hope is always better than despair.

Love will conquer all given the chance
to take root and grow.

09-11-2012

Almost 4 years. Man like Kobe never dies. Still surreal. Still remember where I was, what I was doing when that notification suddenly popped up on my phone. Middle of the night, completely at the opposite end of the world in Bangladesh ğŸ‡§ğŸ‡©. It was way past bedtime and I had a rough day. That news shook me to the last bone in my spine. Didn't have a wink of sleep.

We love our sports here in Bangladesh. Football (what you call soccer) and cricket (baseball's older cousin) rules over here. Among American sports, basketball has a niche following because it is easy to understand and the entertainment value is probably second to none. But names like Kobe Bryant, Michael Jordan, LeBron James resonates to everybody. These names transcend the sport they represent, heck, transcend sports itself.

Some people in life you think would always be there being the kings that they are. Kobe was one of them. Whatever he touched turned into gold. Imagine winning an Oscar a couple of years after retiring as one of the greatest basketball players of all time. Imagine the talent, the sheer will a man needs to have to accomplish these sorts of things.

I still find it hard to come to terms with the fact that Kobe Bryant isnâ€™t walking on this planet amongst us mortals. You know what though. I don't believe one second has gone by in the last four years when the name Kobe Bryant wasnâ€™t remembered by someone at some corner of this planet. Yes man only lived till 41, but if THAT is not an accomplished life, I don't know what is.

Rest in peace Mamba. The world is a worse off place without you.
